HEADWORD: Polaristic
<hw>Po`lar*is"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to,
or exhibiting, poles; having a polar arrangement or disposition; arising
from, or dependent upon, the possession of poles or polar
characteristics; <as>as, <ex>polaristic</ex> antagonism</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polarity</ent>⟦br⟧
